class Solution {
    public boolean canSortArray(int[] nums) {
        int lastCnt = 0;
        int lastGroupMax = 0;
        int curGroupMax = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            int curCnt = Integer.bitCount(num);
            if (curCnt == lastCnt) {
                curGroupMax = Math.max(curGroupMax, num);
            } else {
                lastCnt = curCnt;
                lastGroupMax = curGroupMax;
                curGroupMax = num;
            }
            if (num < lastGroupMax) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

The completed code should return true if it is possible to sort the array with the given condition, and false otherwise. The condition is that if two adjacent elements have the same number of set bits, they can be swapped. The array is considered to be sorted if it is non-decreasing. The function Integer.bitCount(num) is used to get the number of set bits in num. The function Math.max(curGroupMax, num) is used to update the current group maximum with the larger of the current group maximum and the current number. If at any point, a number is less than the last group maximum, the array cannot be sorted, so false is returned. Otherwise, true is returned at the end.

