This problem is a problem of number theory. We need to count the number of numbers in the range [l, r] that are not special, i.e., they do not have exactly 2 proper divisors. We can solve this problem by using the Sieve of Eratosthenes to generate all primes up to 31622 (which is the square root of 10^9), and then for each number in the range [l, r], we can count the number of divisors. If the number of divisors is exactly 2, we increment a counter. At the end, we return the counter.

Here is the completed code:

```java
class Solution {
    private static final int MX = 31622;
    private static final int[] PI = new int[MX + 1];

    static {
        for (int i = 2; i <= MX; i++) {
            if (PI[i] == 0) { // i 是质数
                PI[i] = PI[i - 1] + 1;
                for (int j = i * i; j <= MX; j += i) {
                    PI[j] = -1; // 标记 i 的倍数为合数
                }
            } else {
                PI[i] = PI[i - 1];
            }
        }
    }

    public int nonSpecialCount(int l, int r) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = l; i <= r; i++) {
            if (divisorCount(i) != 2) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }

    private int divisorCount(int n) {
        int count = 1;
        int p = PI[n];
        while (p >= 0 && n % PI[p] == 0) {
            n /= PI[p];
            count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

